<define-tag description>security update</define-tag>
<define-tag moreinfo>
<p>Matthias Gerstner discovered that PackageKit, a DBus abstraction layer
for simple software management tasks, contains an authentication bypass
flaw allowing users without privileges to install local packages.</p>

<p>For the stable distribution (stretch), this problem has been fixed in
version 1.1.5-2+deb9u1.</p>

<p>We recommend that you upgrade your packagekit packages.</p>

<p>For the detailed security status of packagekit please refer to its
security tracker page at:
<a href="https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/packagekit">https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/packagekit</a></p>
</define-tag>

